    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions About Bubble Wrap</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 my-10">
        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">How long can bubble wrap be stored before losing effectiveness?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Bubble wrap maintains effectiveness indefinitely when stored properly in dry conditions away from direct sunlight. UV exposure and heat can degrade plastic over extended periods, so store in cool, dark locations. Properly stored bubble wrap can be used for years without performance degradation. Most businesses use inventory fast enough that storage duration isn't a concern.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">Can bubble wrap be recycled?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Standard bubble wrap can be recycled in many facilities, though some require it to be separated from packaging materials. Check with your local recycling program for acceptance guidelines. Many businesses save used bubble wrap for reuse in future shipments, maximizing value. Eco-friendly bubble wrap made from recycled materials is also available if environmental impact is a priority.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">Does bubble wrap work for all types of items?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Bubble wrap is highly versatile and works for most items. However, sharp objects may puncture bubbles—consider combining bubble wrap with corrugated cardboard for sharp items. Extremely heavy machinery might benefit from additional protective layers. For specialized items, contact Quinocycle's team for recommendations on optimal protection combinations.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">What width bubble wrap should I order for my items?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Choose roll width based on item size. Wider rolls (60-100cm) work well for large items and machinery. Narrower rolls (30-50cm) provide flexibility for various item sizes. For general e-commerce operations with diverse item sizes, 50cm width offers the best balance. Contact Quinocycle to discuss your specific products and get a recommendation.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
